This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of propositional logic and fuzzy propositions, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed architecture to robotic manipulation tasks suggests that it could fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions conducting a user study to solicit expert policies, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) or computer vision (cs.CV) techniques to interpret the policies provided by humans.
